{{Han etyl}}
''{{w|Shuowen}}'' suggests that it is an {{liushu|i|nocap=1}} from {{zh-l|*仄|to tilt}} flipped – something that can be tilted and turned; something round.

Unrelated to the right component of characters like {{zh-l|*執}} and {{zh-l|*孰}}, which comes from {{zh-l|*丮}}.

